This workflow does not re-implement GapMind. It orchestrates and containerizes
the original PaperBLAST/GapMind programs, which do the science. Please cite the
GapMind papers (see CITATION.cff) in any publication that uses this workflow.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Wrapped software
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PaperBLAST / GapMind — Morgan N. Price, Arkin lab, Lawrence Berkeley National
  Laboratory. GPL-3.0. https://github.com/morgannprice/PaperBLAST
  The container clones this at a pinned commit and runs its scripts unmodified
  except for shebang/interpreter normalization and tool path wiring (which do not
  change results). Corresponding source for the container is that upstream
  repository plus this repository (containers/).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party tools in the container (each under its own license)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- DIAMOND        GPL-3.0            https://github.com/bbuchfink/diamond
- HMMER          BSD-3-Clause       http://hmmer.org
- Nextflow       Apache-2.0         https://www.nextflow.io
- Singularity/Apptainer, Docker     BSD-3 / Apache-2.0 (runtime, not bundled)
- Perl + CPAN modules (DBI, DBD::SQLite, BioPerl, LWP, XML::LibXML, CGI, ...)
                 Artistic/GPL (Perl) and each module's license
- NumPy, SciPy, Matplotlib          BSD-3 / PSF-style
- usearch 11 (optional; only for the amino-acid known-gap step)
    The binary is taken from the public-domain mirror at
    https://github.com/rcedgar/usearch_old_binaries . CONFIRM its redistribution
    terms before shipping a public image, or build without it and run with
    --knownsim false (also required for an ARM-only image).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Databases (downloaded at run time, not redistributed here)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The prebuilt curated + steps databases are fetched from
papers.genomics.lbl.gov at run time. They are derived from the PaperBLAST
characterized set and public sources (Swiss-Prot, BRENDA, TIGRFam, Pfam, EcoCyc,
CharProtDB, and others). If you archive a specific database snapshot for
reproducibility, confirm the redistribution terms of LBL and of those sources.

